      <h2>Sector Breakdown & Category Averages</h2>
      <p>A crucial part of understanding a dividend-paying asset's risk profile is analyzing its sector allocations. Funds concentrated in highly cyclical sectors may offer higher yields but come with increased volatility and the potential for dividend cuts during economic downturns. Conversely, assets with broad diversification or a focus on stable sectors like consumer staples and utilities tend to offer more reliable, albeit sometimes lower, dividend distributions.</p>


