        </ul>
      </div>


      <p>When compared to the broader category averages, PENNY exhibits distinct characteristics. Typically, average dividend yields for large-cap equity funds hover around the 1.5% to 2.5% mark. High-yield focused funds and certain actively managed income ETFs can push average yields to 7% or higher. Evaluating how this specific asset compares to these benchmarks helps identify whether its current yield compensates adequately for its risk profile, expense ratio, and historical volatility.</p>

      <h2>Recent Ex-Dividend Dates</h2>
      <p>The ex-dividend date is a critical deadline for income investors. To be eligible to receive the upcoming dividend payout, you must purchase the stock or ETF before the ex-dividend date. If you buy shares on or after this date, the previous owner will receive the dividend. Tracking these dates closely is essential for timing purchases and maximizing short-term yield.</p>


